<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Random number, and best way to get a seed value?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11443&amp;p=131306#p131306"><![CDATA[
After setting up my title screen, I run a loop polling for the user to press start. Each loop I tick the PRNG as well.<br />This works very well, since the loop will run maybe 100 times per frame, and on real hardware, they could press it at any time during the frame (~6000 possible values in any given second).<br />On an emulator, it's really no better than doing it once per frame, since input is typically internally polled once per frame by the emulator (~60 possible values in any given second).<br /><br />If using this method, make sure the start button is released before you start polling, otherwise someone could hold it down on reset to get a consistent seed.<br /><br />As a fun aside, Final Fantasy IV on the GBA used to seed its random number generator based on the number of seconds (not frames) spent on the title screen. It was quite easy to make specific battles happen reliably from a save point loaded from the title screen.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Fri Jul 18, 2014 3:48 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
