<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11443&amp;p=131300#p131300"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Random number, and best way to get a seed value?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11443&amp;p=131300#p131300"><![CDATA[
I've always liked the idea of using the wait for vblank to seed a random number.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">mainloop:<br />lda vblanktimer<br />mainloop.vblank:<br />inc randomseed<br />cmp vblanktimer<br />beq mainloop.vblank<br /></div><br /><br />Basically, because your program will probably take a somewhat different amount of frame time each frame, the number of cycles left until vblank is different. And thus the number of times that loop is run is sort of random. And so, randomseed is incremented a somewhat random number of times.<br /><br />Edit: I used the random number generator in the top of <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=103974#p103974" class="postlink">this post</a> for Galaxy NES and it was random enough for that purpose. I ran it every frame, and then when it was needed.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3504">Kasumi</a> — Fri Jul 18, 2014 2:21 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
